definition: to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc

sentences.english: He's a pre-eminent authority in the field of bio-chemistry.
sentences.chinese: 他是生化學這個領域最傑出的權威人士。

sentences.english: Her father, Squire Dickinson, was a lawyer and prominent community member.
sentences.chinese: 狄金森是律師，也是傑出的社區成員。

sentences.english: RU Shu-hua is an outstanding educator in the history of Chinese higher education.
sentences.chinese: 胡庶華是我國近現代一位傑出的教育家。

sentences.english: Yochanan ben Zakkai was the youngest and most distinguished disciple of Rabbi Hillel.
sentences.chinese: 約翰南是希列爾拉比最年輕最傑出的學生。

sentences.english: Thank you to the Great Leader and artist in our city, Thank you Mr. LU.

sentences.english: Kuo Hong-chih has had an outstanding performance this season.

sentences.english: Plum green glaze is a outstanding celadon glaze originated in Longquan Kiln in Southern Song Dynasty.

sentences.english: Christopher Marlowe is one of the outstanding representatives of English Renaissance dramatists.

sentences.english: Liuyuxi is an outstanding statesman and exiling poem in middle of Tang Dynasty .

sentences.english: He was a master of administration and diplomacy .

sentences.english: He is an eminent scholar, but he always keeps his knowledge in the background.

sentences.english: My friend Mike Litman wrote an outstanding article for his ezine this week.

sentences.english: That naughty little boy has grown into an outstanding bridge engineer.
sentences.chinese: 那個調皮的小男孩已成長爲一名傑出的橋樑一程師。

sentences.english: I was chosen as one of“The Big Ten Prominent Youths”of Beijing in 1996.
sentences.chinese: 我1996年被評爲“北京市十大傑出青年”。

sentences.english: Na received support from another prominent female politician, Park Geun-hye.
sentences.chinese: 羅卿瑗得到了另外一位傑出的女政治家朴槿惠的支持。
